{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Please place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata (see [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]) -->
{{Lua|Module:Fba}}
==Description==
<code><nowiki>{{fb|nation|variant|size=optional|name=optional}}</nowiki></code>

Produces a flag icon attached to a wikilinked national football association article. The list of article titles of the national football associations is located at [[Template:Fba/list]].

'''Parameters'''
*''nation''&nbsp;– Use either the name of the nation or the three-letter country code as used by [[List of FIFA country codes|FIFA]]
*''variant'' (optional)&nbsp;– Specifies an alternate (historical) flag to use.  This parameter is documented by the appropriate template in [[:Category:Country data templates]].
*''size'' (optional)&nbsp;– Can be used to change the flag icon size (use sparingly!)
*''name'' (optional)&nbsp;– Can be used to change the wikilink display text
**Setting the parameter to {{para|name|full}} will display the full association name instead of the country
**Setting the parameter to {{para|name|code}} will display the association code instead of the country name
*''old'' (optional)&nbsp;- When given a value (e.g. "<code>yes</code>"/"<code>y</code>"/"<code>1</code>"), will link to the country's former football association (only applies to Brunei and Kenya)
*''wrap'' (optional)&nbsp;- When given a value (e.g. "<code>yes</code>"/"<code>y</code>"/"<code>1</code>"), the text is allowed to wrap

==Examples==
*<code><nowiki>{{fba|Argentina}}</nowiki></code> → {{fba|Argentina}}
*<code><nowiki>{{fba|ENG}}</nowiki></code> → {{fba|ENG}}
*<code><nowiki>{{fba|Italy|1861}}</nowiki></code> → {{fba|Italy|1861}}
*<code><nowiki>{{fba|GER|name=GER}}</nowiki></code> → {{fba|GER|name=GER}}
*<code><nowiki>{{fba|ESP|name=full}}</nowiki></code> → {{fba|ESP|name=full}}
*<code><nowiki>{{fba|Mexico|name=code}}</nowiki></code> → {{fba|Mexico|name=code}}

==Alternative to avoid Wikipedia's [[WP:PEIS|Post-expand include size]] limit==
Pages with many flag icons may come close to or exceed Wikipedia's [[WP:PEIS|Post-expand include size]] limit.  In these cases consider using lua modules instead:
* {{module link|flag|{{BASEPAGENAME}}}} is a wrapper for [[Module:Flagg]] that can reduce the include size when invoked directly. For basic use, {{tlx|{{BASEPAGENAME}}|''country''}} can be replaced with {{mlx|flag|{{BASEPAGENAME}}|''country''}}.

==Parameters==
{{TemplateDataHeader}}

<templatedata>
{
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"label": "Nation",
			"description": "Use either the name of the nation or the three-letter country code as used by FIFA",
			"example": "Argentina",
			"type": "string",
			"required": true
		},
		"variant": {
			"aliases": [
				"2"
			],
			"label": "Flag variant",
			"description": "Specifies an alternate (historical) flag to use. This parameter is documented by the appropriate template in Category:Country data templates.",
			"example": "1861",
			"type": "string"
		},
		"size": {
			"label": "Icon size",
			"description": "Can be used to change the flag icon size (use sparingly!)"
		},
		"name": {
			"label": "Link text",
			"description": "Can be used to change the wikilink display text"
		},
		"old": {
			"label": "Old",
			"description": "When given a value (e.g. \"yes\"/\"y\"/\"1\"), will link to the country's former football association (only applies to Brunei and Kenya)",
			"type": "unknown"
		}
	},
	"description": "Produces a flag icon attached to a wikilinked national football association article.",
	"paramOrder": [
		"1",
		"variant",
		"size",
		"name",
		"old"
	],
	"format": "inline"
}
</templatedata>

==See also==
*[[Template:fbaicon]]&nbsp;– for rendering the flag on its own, with a wikilink to the national association team page.
*[[Template:fb]]&nbsp;– for linking to men's national football teams

